This paper deals with the problem of learning from opinionated documents, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of active learning algorithms, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper focuses on the challenges of working with limited labels, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data mining (cs.SI) research.
